@NODE "Author's other programs" "Author's other programs"

  @{B}Author's other programs
  @{U}                                                                      @{UU}@{UB}
  
  If you enjoy using this program, you will probably want to check out
  the other programs released by its author.
  
  You can find the following freeware programs on the author's WEB site
  or on any Aminet file archive Worldwide:
  
  - @{B}ctrequest.library - a shared requester toolkit library@{UB}
    A powerful requester builder engine that uses the latest technology
    offered by AmigaOS and allows developers to create new style and
    fully font and 1x1 resolution adaptive requesters with minimum
    efforts, while the look and key features of requesters can be fully
    configured by the users of the systems.

  - @{B}CTRPatch - requester improver@{UB}
    This system patch program replaces AmigaOS EasyRequestArgs() style
    requesters with fully customized CTRequest requesters. The program
    also features a fully user-configurable "assign wedge" solution that
    is designed to work in multi-language systems.

  - @{B}DesktopToilet@{UB}
    Removes drawers/files and their icons and also cleans up Workbench
    by closing all open windows whose titles are not matched in an
    exclude-list.
  
  - @{B}VSM, Virtual Screen Manager for Amiga@{UB}
    Explore the powerful virtual screen support in AmigaOS by using
    this AREXX-aware program.
  
  - @{B}Ned@{UB}
    Ned is a handy AmigaOS commodity that allows you to close the
    active window by pressing the ESCAPE key.
    Furthermore, it can send intuition events to the active window and
    thus making it iconified or execute an AmigaOS executable file on
    a press of the ESCAPE key.
    Ned gives you a single interface for closing windows.
  
  - @{B}RandomE@{UB}
    RandomE is a flexible CLI/Shell tool that randomly executes
    AmigaDOS Executable lines from a List-File.
    RandomE fully supports the powerful pattern matching mechanism of
    AmigaDOS, enabling some very efficient operations like playing
    audio files in many different random orders.
  
@ENDNODE
